## 10. Analysis Workflow Checklists

### Quick Triage Checklist (5 minutes)

```
[ ] Extract raw email headers
[ ] Check SPF, DKIM, DMARC results in Authentication-Results header
[ ] Verify From: domain matches sending server in Received: headers
[ ] Check if Reply-To: differs from From:
[ ] Note any suspicious subject line patterns
[ ] Identify links — do they match the claimed sender's domain?
[ ] Note any attachments and their file types
[ ] Search sender domain age (WHOIS)
[ ] Check sender IP in AbuseIPDB or VirusTotal
```

### Deep Investigation Checklist (30–60 minutes)

**Headers:**
```
[ ] Trace full Received: chain from bottom to top
[ ] Identify originating IP and geolocate it
[ ] Check originating IP reputation (VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB, Shodan)
[ ] Verify Message-ID domain matches From: domain
[ ] Check for X-Originating-IP header
[ ] Look for header anomalies (forged timestamps, private IPs in external hops)
```

**Authentication:**
```
[ ] Document SPF result and check SPF record manually (dig TXT)
[ ] Document DKIM result and verify selector key exists (dig TXT selector._domainkey.domain)
[ ] Document DMARC result and check policy (p=none/quarantine/reject)
[ ] Determine if email alignment passed (RFC5322.From must align with SPF/DKIM domain for DMARC)
```

**Sender Investigation:**
```
[ ] Check domain registration date (WHOIS)
[ ] Check domain reputation (VirusTotal, Cisco Talos)
[ ] Verify sender IP is authorized by SPF record
[ ] Check if domain is in OpenPhish / PhishTank
[ ] Search for related infrastructure (PassiveTotal, RiskIQ)
```

**URL Analysis:**
```
[ ] Extract all URLs from email body (raw source)
[ ] Expand any URL shorteners
[ ] Scan each URL in VirusTotal
[ ] Screenshot each URL in URLScan.io
[ ] Check SSL certificate details
[ ] Identify if page is a credential harvester
[ ] Check for redirects and final landing page
```

**Attachment Analysis:**
```
[ ] Calculate SHA256 hash of each attachment
[ ] Search hash in VirusTotal / Hybrid Analysis
[ ] Identify true file type (magic bytes vs. extension)
[ ] Submit to Any.run or Cuckoo for behavioral analysis
[ ] If Office doc: run olevba to extract macros
[ ] If PDF: run pdfid.py and pdf-parser.py
[ ] Document any C2 communications or dropped files
```

**Impact Assessment:**
```
[ ] Identify how many users received the email
[ ] Determine if any users clicked links
[ ] Determine if any users downloaded/opened attachments
[ ] Check email gateway logs for similar campaigns
[ ] Identify any credential submissions or data exfiltration
```

### Response Actions Checklist

```
[ ] Preserve original email evidence (.eml / .msg)
[ ] Block sender IP at email gateway
[ ] Block sender domain at email gateway and DNS
[ ] Block malicious URLs at web proxy / DNS filter
[ ] Submit URLs to Google Safe Browsing / Microsoft SSCS
[ ] Submit URLs to PhishTank / OpenPhish
[ ] Add IOCs (domains, IPs, hashes, URLs) to SIEM
[ ] Recall/delete email from all user mailboxes (if supported by platform)
[ ] Notify affected users and instruct them to change passwords if they clicked
[ ] Escalate to incident response if credential compromise is suspected
[ ] Document findings in ticketing system
[ ] Share IOCs with threat intel community (MISP, OTX)
```

